Package gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.converter

Class Normalizer

java.lang.Object
gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.converter.Normalizer
public class Normalizer extends Object
This class supports basic normalization of resources within a bundle when two or more resources of the same type may be created having the same identity.

Audacious Inquiry

  • Method Details

    • normalizeResources

      public static void normalizeResources(org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Bundle bundle)
      Merge duplicated resources in the bundle. This is the main entry point for normalization processing. In creating resources, V2toFHIR library may create duplicates for resources created from names, identifiers, or other V2 datatypes. This method will combine duplicates and references into a single resource that represents the object.
      Parameters:
      bundle - The bundle to normalize.

    • codesEqual

      public static boolean codesEqual(org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.CodeableConcept first, org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.CodeableConcept later)
      Compare two codes for compatibility. If one or the other is null but not both, they are NOT compatible (unlike identifier).
      Parameters:
      first - The first code
      later - The later code
      Returns:
      true if the two values are compatible
